<br>
The SoV error (in my opinion) was the massive upgrading of ToV loot.  I do think it needed to be upgraded, I just believe that they went too far.<br>
<br>
The whole risk vs. reward is complete BS.  This isn't Fear the first few weeks where corpses DID rot because of the inability to retrieve them.  At best its 'risk vs. inconvenience'.  Its really &quot;how much more Uber should we make you because you are first/best&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, more guilds are going 'North' but the nature of the zone will make the ensuing arguments over it into a thoroughly unpleasant situation.  And unless 'near equivalent' upgrades are found in Luclin I forsee NToV being contested for a long time.<br>
<br>
There will ALWAYS be cachet and real value in the *best* gear.  The problem that exists now is that the &quot;second best&quot; gear isn't even in the same league in many cases.<br>
<br>
Some of the upgrades were done well I think.  The CP of Fiery Might for example.  It is the BP I would most want.  I would strive for it, but I don't feel shafted if I have to 'settle' for a Shining BP.<br>
<br>
But then you have these jumps:<br>
<br>
Spirit Caller's Vambraces: Wt 5.00. +24 AC, +1 Str, +1 Sta, +3 Dex, +3 Wis, +10 HP, +15 Mana<br>
<br>
Onyx Chain Sleeves: Wt 0.00. +38 AC, +4 Str, +4 Sta, +4 Agi, +4 Dex, +4 Wis, +4 Int, +4 Cha, +6 vsMg, +6 vsFire, +6 vsCold, +6 vsPos, +6 vsDis, +40 HP, +40 Mana<br>
<br>
Thats just one example, don't even get me started on the obscene monk wearable items ;-)<br>
<br>
The other error, imo, is the specifics of primal weapons.  It would have been much better to have made them primary only and have the proc last a shorter duration.  It would then be a temporary stage in ones career.  The stopping point that most reach somewhere between ToV armor farms and NToV clearings.  A 1 minute proc on a primary hand makes it very nice for that point, but keeps it from being the 'end game' gear that it now is.  (It would also fix the 'primal' advantage that DW have over 2h users). <br>
<br>
People are motivated when they can see that they can make progress towards their 'goals'.  And the current structure of Velious does not do that.  It stratifies players into the haves/have nots in a way that I think is bad for the game.<br>
<br>
Others thoughts are welcome in response.  This isn't coming from what I would consider a 'whining' perspective, but rather from a person who has recently seen *much* hostility on his server brought about by such loot.  Hostility that at times makes it more aggravating than fun to play this game.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Kether <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uketherami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kether Am I</A> at: 12/15/01 5:12:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uavalssra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalssra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/15/01 5:48:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thoughts on Velious flaws to motivate players</span><hr size=1> Id really liked to have seen 2 or 3 new zones in sol that are as difficult and contain the same quality loot as North tov but are on totally different factions which would make it impossible for one guild to attempt to farm items from two of the new zones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabatoirredux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AbatoirRedux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/15/01 7:38:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> totaly agree-</span><hr size=1> and you didnt even go to the really nice item to compare to.. the sleaves off Vulak blow the Onyx away by as much as Onyx blows away spirt callers :/<br>
